    <title ixia_locid="1">Installing Software on<ph ixia_locid="828" product="tis_cpe">
            Controller-1</ph><ph ixia_locid="1032" product="tis_lvm"> Controller-1  or a Compute
            Host</ph><ph ixia_locid="1033" product="tis_ceph"> Controller-1 or a Compute or Storage
            Host</ph></title>
    <shortdesc ixia_locid="2">You must use <nameliteral ixia_locid="3">controller-0</nameliteral> to
        install software on other hosts.</shortdesc>
    <prolog>
        <author ixia_locid="4">Jim Owens</author>
        <author ixia_locid="5">Tom Towle</author>
        <author ixia_locid="6">Pedro Sanchez</author>
    </prolog>
    <taskbody>
        <context id="context_N10039_N10036_N10001" ixia_locid="830" product="tis_cpe">
            <p ixia_locid="831">For a CPE system, the only additional host used is <nameliteral ixia_locid="832">controller-1</nameliteral>.</p>
        </context>
        <prereq conref="ifl1462548530418.xml#ifl1462548530418/prerequisites" id="prereq_N1002B_N10028_N10001" ixia_locid="7"/>
        <steps id="steps_nvd_tz5_k4">
            <step id="boot-node" ixia_locid="569">
                <cmd ixia_locid="570">Power on the host.</cmd>
                <info ixia_locid="571">
                    <p ixia_locid="572"><note id="note_N10395_N10392_N1038E_N1037E_N100E2_N10029_N10001" ixia_locid="778" product="tis_nonregion">
                            <p ixia_locid="779">To ensure you can correctly identify hosts as you
                                install them, power on and configure each new node one at a
                                time.</p>
                        </note>With <nameliteral ixia_locid="573">controller-0</nameliteral>
                        running, start the host.</p>
                    <!-- p><nameliteral>controller-0</nameliteral> accepts the PXE request from the
                        host node, configures the node's IP address, and pushes a network
                        bootstrap program.</p -->
                    <!-- draft-comment>Jim - too much detail?</draft-comment -->
                    <p ixia_locid="574"><draft-comment author="jowens" ixia_locid="780">US63465
                            branding removed from screen</draft-comment>The host boots from the
                        network and then displays a message that it is waiting to be configured.</p>
                    <fig id="fig_N100BC_N100A9_N100A1_N10091_N10024_N10001" ixia_locid="575">
                        <image href="jow1404333500016.image" id="image_whb_vjd_gn" ixia_locid="576"/>
                    </fig>
                </info>
            </step>
            <step id="horizon-open-edit-host" ixia_locid="849">
                <cmd ixia_locid="850">Open the Edit Host dialog box to begin provisioning the new
                    host.</cmd>
                <substeps id="substeps_cdx_ds4_k4">
                    <substep id="open-hosts-list" ixia_locid="423">
                        <cmd id="open-hosts-lists-cmd" ixia_locid="424">Display the available hosts
                            in the system.</cmd>
                        <info ixia_locid="43">
                            <p ixia_locid="426">Select the <wintitle ixia_locid="429">Hosts</wintitle> tab on the <wintitle ixia_locid="1034">Host Inventory</wintitle>
                                page, available from <menucascade ixia_locid="1035">
                                    <uicontrol ixia_locid="45">Admin</uicontrol>
                                    <uicontrol ixia_locid="427">Platform</uicontrol>
                                    <uicontrol ixia_locid="428">Host Inventory</uicontrol>
                                </menucascade> on the left-hand pane.</p>
                            <p id="open-hosts-lists-new-node" ixia_locid="49"><draft-comment author="jowens" ixia_locid="826">US77470 update for new
                                    UnProvisioned Hosts list.</draft-comment>The new node is listed
                                in the <nameliteral ixia_locid="827">UnProvisioned
                                    Hosts</nameliteral> list.</p>
                            <fig id="fig_N10108_N100E4_N100D7_N100D3_N100CB_N10091_N10024_N10001" ixia_locid="431">
                                <image href="aqw1462549098049.image" id="image_yld_2zd_gn" ixia_locid="432"/>
                            </fig>
                        </info>
                    </substep>
                    <substep id="click-edit-hosts" ixia_locid="790">
                        <cmd ixia_locid="791">Click <uicontrol ixia_locid="58">Edit Host</uicontrol>
                            for the new host.</cmd>
                        <stepresult ixia_locid="792">
                            <p ixia_locid="108">The <wintitle ixia_locid="131">Edit Host</wintitle>
                                window appears.</p>
                            <fig id="fig_N10129_N1011E_N10116_N100D3_N100CB_N10091_N10024_N10001" ixia_locid="59">
                                <image href="jow1404333503033.image" id="image_wfz_h54_k4" ixia_locid="60"/>
                            </fig>
                        </stepresult>
                    </substep>
                </substeps>
            </step>
            <step id="assign-personality" ixia_locid="854">
                <cmd ixia_locid="855"><draft-comment author="jowens" ixia_locid="1015">US84106 and
                        US85273 steps revised for personality subtypes; CGTS-5792 step
                        conditionalized for different installation guides</draft-comment>Assign the
                    appropriate personality to the host.</cmd>
                <info ixia_locid="1046" product="tis_cpe">
                    <p ixia_locid="1047">For a CPE system, select <nameliteral ixia_locid="1048">Controller</nameliteral>.</p>
                </info>
                <info ixia_locid="856" product="tis_std">
                    <p ixia_locid="857">By default, the <option ixia_locid="949">Compute</option>
                        personality is selected. Use the <uicontrol ixia_locid="858">Personality</uicontrol> drop-down menu to specify the type of host you
                        are installing (<option ixia_locid="950">Controller</option> or <option ixia_locid="951">Storage</option>).</p>
                    <note id="note_N1014B_N1012E_N1011D_N10052_N10038_N10001" ixia_locid="1029">
                        <p ixia_locid="1030">The <option ixia_locid="1031">Storage</option> option
                            is available only if an infrastructure network is present.</p>
                    </note>
                </info>
                <stepresult ixia_locid="952">
                    <p ixia_locid="953">The window is updated for the personality.</p>
                    <p ixia_locid="873" product="tis_std">For a controller host:</p>
                    <fig id="fig_d4q_jc2_px" ixia_locid="954">
                        <image href="jow1447960401773.image" id="image_e4q_jc2_px" ixia_locid="955">
                            <alt ixia_locid="956">TiS Edit Host: Personality Controller</alt>
                        </image>
                    </fig>
                    <p ixia_locid="877" product="tis_ceph">For a storage host:</p>
                    <fig id="fig_f4q_jc2_px" ixia_locid="957" product="tis_ceph">
                        <image href="jow1404848586688.image" id="image_g4q_jc2_px" ixia_locid="958">
                            <alt ixia_locid="959">TiS Edit Host: Personality Storage</alt>
                        </image>
                    </fig>
                </stepresult>
            </step>
            <step id="step_N10175_N10052_N10038_N10001" ixia_locid="960">
                <cmd ixia_locid="961">Complete the remaining fields on the <uicontrol ixia_locid="962">Host Info</uicontrol>
                    tab.</cmd>
                <info ixia_locid="963">
                    <dl>
                        <dlentry ixia_locid="964" product="tis_std">
                            <dt ixia_locid="965"><uicontrol ixia_locid="966">Performance
                                    Profile</uicontrol></dt>
                            <dd ixia_locid="967">
                                <p ixia_locid="1036">(shown only for a <uicontrol ixia_locid="969">Compute</uicontrol> personality) The performance
                                    characteristic of the host. </p>
                                <p ixia_locid="1037">Accept the default value (<option ixia_locid="972">Standard</option>). Other values are
                                    reserved for future use.</p>
                            </dd>
                        </dlentry>
                        <dlentry ixia_locid="982" product="tis_std">
                            <dt ixia_locid="983"><uicontrol ixia_locid="984">Host
                                Name</uicontrol></dt>
                            <dd ixia_locid="985">
                                <p ixia_locid="986">(shown only for a <uicontrol ixia_locid="987">Compute</uicontrol> personality) An optional custom name
                                    for the compute host. The name appears in the Host Inventory and
                                    other places where the host is listed, and can be used in most
                                    CLI commands to specify the host.</p>
                            </dd>
                        </dlentry>
                        <dlentry ixia_locid="988" product="tis_ceph">
                            <dt ixia_locid="989"><uicontrol ixia_locid="990">Personality
                                    Sub-Type</uicontrol></dt>
                            <dd ixia_locid="991">
                                <p ixia_locid="992">(shown only for a <uicontrol ixia_locid="993">Storage</uicontrol> personality) The role of the host in a
                                    storage cluster. The following sub-types are available:</p>
                                <dl>
                                    <dlentry ixia_locid="994">
                                        <dt ixia_locid="995"><option ixia_locid="996">Ceph
                                                backing</option></dt>
                                        <dd ixia_locid="997">
                                            <p ixia_locid="998">Use this for a standard storage
                                                configuration.</p>
                                        </dd>
                                    </dlentry>
                                    <dlentry ixia_locid="999">
                                        <dt ixia_locid="1000"><option ixia_locid="1001">Ceph
                                                tiering</option></dt>
                                        <dd ixia_locid="1002">
                                            <p ixia_locid="1003">Use this when implementing a cache
                                                tier.</p>
                                            <note id="note_N101B0_N1019A_N10182_N10179_N1016D_N1010D_N10066_N1005C_N10059_N10039_N10001" ixia_locid="1016">
                                                <p ixia_locid="1017">You cannot add a <nameliteral ixia_locid="1018">Ceph tiering</nameliteral> host
                                                  until cache tiering is configured on the system.
                                                  For more information, see <ph ixia_locid="1019" otherprops="printonly"><cite ixia_locid="1020">Titanium Server System Administration:
                                                  </cite></ph><cite ixia_locid="1021"><ph ixia_locid="1022"><xref href="siv1474312502430.xml" ixia_locid="1023"/></ph></cite>. In addition, the system must
                                                  already have a <nameliteral ixia_locid="1024">Ceph
                                                  backing</nameliteral> host.</p>
                                            </note>
                                        </dd>
                                    </dlentry>
                                </dl>
                            </dd>
                        </dlentry>
                        <dlentry ixia_locid="1009">
                            <dt ixia_locid="1010"><uicontrol ixia_locid="1011">Location</uicontrol></dt>
                            <dd ixia_locid="1012">
                                <p ixia_locid="1013">An optional description of the host location
                                    (for example, its site or rack position) to help manage large
                                    systems.</p>
                            </dd>
                        </dlentry>
                    </dl>
                </info>
            </step>
            <step id="horizon-set-optional-parameters" ixia_locid="879">
                <cmd importance="optional" ixia_locid="892">Set the installation parameters for the
                    node.</cmd>
                <info ixia_locid="893">
                    <note id="note_N107F3_N107F0_N107DF_N100F5_N10029_N10001" ixia_locid="894" type="caution">
                        <p ixia_locid="895">If the host uses any console port other than
                                <nameliteral ixia_locid="896">ttys0</nameliteral> for output
                            display, you must change settings on the <uicontrol ixia_locid="897">Installation Parameters</uicontrol> tab to ensure that the host
                            uses the correct port.</p>
                    </note>
                    <p ixia_locid="898">On the <uicontrol ixia_locid="899">Host Info</uicontrol>
                        tab:</p>
                    <ul id="ul_spk_jmx_mx">
                        <li ixia_locid="900">
                            <p ixia_locid="901">Type a physical <uicontrol ixia_locid="902">Location</uicontrol> for the node to help identify it.</p>
                        </li>
                        <li ixia_locid="903">
                            <p ixia_locid="904"><draft-comment author="rstone" ixia_locid="905">US63466 adds </draft-comment>Specify whether to enable
                                    <uicontrol ixia_locid="906">Serial Console Data Carrier
                                    Detect</uicontrol>.</p>
                            <p ixia_locid="907">Select this option to have any active console
                                session automatically logged out when the serial console cable is
                                disconnected. The server must support data carrier detect on the
                                serial console port.</p>
                        </li>
                    </ul>
                    <p ixia_locid="908">On the <uicontrol ixia_locid="909">Installation
                            Parameters</uicontrol> tab:</p>
                    <fig id="fig_wfs_qkx_mx" ixia_locid="910">
                        <image href="jow1443358337894.image" id="image_xfs_qkx_mx" ixia_locid="911">
                            <alt ixia_locid="912">TiS Edit Host Installation Parameters</alt>
                        </image>
                    </fig>
                    <dl>
                        <dlentry ixia_locid="913">
                            <dt ixia_locid="914"><uicontrol ixia_locid="915">Boot
                                Device</uicontrol></dt>
                            <dd ixia_locid="916">
                                <p ixia_locid="917">is the host device for boot partition, relative
                                    to <filepath ixia_locid="918">/dev</filepath>. The default is
                                        <option ixia_locid="919">sda</option>.</p>
                            </dd>
                        </dlentry>
                        <dlentry ixia_locid="1025">
                            <dt ixia_locid="1026"><uicontrol ixia_locid="1027">Rootfs
                                    Device</uicontrol></dt>
                            <dd ixia_locid="1028">
                                <p ixia_locid="924">is the host device for rootfs partition,
                                    relative to<filepath ixia_locid="925"> /dev</filepath>. The
                                    default is <option ixia_locid="926">sda</option>.</p>
                            </dd>
                        </dlentry>
                        <dlentry ixia_locid="927">
                            <dt ixia_locid="928"><uicontrol ixia_locid="929">Installation
                                    Output</uicontrol></dt>
                            <dd ixia_locid="930">
                                <p ixia_locid="931">is the format for console output on the host
                                        (<option ixia_locid="932">text</option> or <option ixia_locid="933">graphical</option>). The default is <option ixia_locid="934">text</option>.</p>
                                <note id="note_N108C1_N108A9_N1089D_N10858_N107F0_N107DF_N100F5_N10029_N10001" ixia_locid="935">
                                    <p ixia_locid="936"><draft-comment author="jowens" ixia_locid="1038">CGTS-5076
                                            graphical installation disabled</draft-comment>The
                                            <option ixia_locid="937">graphical</option> option
                                        currently has no effect. Text-based installation is used
                                        regardless of this setting.</p>
                                </note>
                            </dd>
                        </dlentry>
                        <dlentry ixia_locid="940">
                            <dt ixia_locid="941"><uicontrol ixia_locid="942">Console</uicontrol></dt>
                            <dd ixia_locid="943">
                                <p ixia_locid="1039">is the output device to use for message display
                                    on the host (for example, <option ixia_locid="945">tty0</option>). The default is <option ixia_locid="946">ttys0,
                                        115200</option>. </p>
                                <note id="note_N103A9_N10396_N1038A_N10309_N10299_N1028E_N10057_N1003D_N10001" ixia_locid="1040">
                                    <p ixia_locid="1041">This setting is <i ixia_locid="947">not</i>
                                        updated automatically to reflect changes to the <uicontrol ixia_locid="948">Installation Output</uicontrol>
                                        setting.</p>
                                </note>
                            </dd>
                        </dlentry>
                    </dl>
                </info>
            </step>
            <step id="horizon-save-settings" ixia_locid="890">
                <cmd ixia_locid="891">Save the settings.</cmd>
                <substeps id="substeps_nkj_xkx_mx">
                    <substep ixia_locid="67">
                        <cmd id="cmd-save-personality" ixia_locid="68">Click <uicontrol ixia_locid="69">Save</uicontrol> to initialize and configure the new
                            node.</cmd>
                        <stepresult ixia_locid="109">
                            <p id="p-save-personality" ixia_locid="562"><draft-comment author="jowens" ixia_locid="783">US63465 branding removed from
                                    screen</draft-comment>The node is restarted automatically, and a
                                display-device menu appears on the node console.</p>
                            <fig id="fig_qkj_xkx_mx" ixia_locid="563">
                                <image href="jow1412193160572.image" id="image_rkj_xkx_mx" ixia_locid="770">
                                    <alt ixia_locid="771">Titanium Server Controller Node
                                        Install</alt>
                                </image>
                            </fig>
                        </stepresult>
                    </substep>
                    <substep id="wait_for_login_prompt" ixia_locid="116">
                        <cmd ixia_locid="117">Wait while the node is configured and rebooted.</cmd>
                        <info ixia_locid="118">
                            <p ixia_locid="1042">Up to 20 minutes may be required for a reboot.</p>
                            <p ixia_locid="1043">The time required to configure and reboot controller-1 depends on the
                                secondary disk partition size. Larger partitions require more time
                                for synchronization with controller-0. Fore more information on DRBD
                                synchronization and tuning, see <xref href="gri1467382322806.xml" ixia_locid="1044"/>.</p>
                            <p ixia_locid="1045">When the reboot is complete, the node is reported as
                                    <uicontrol ixia_locid="123">Locked</uicontrol>, <uicontrol ixia_locid="802">Disabled</uicontrol>, and <uicontrol ixia_locid="127">Online</uicontrol>.</p>
                            <note id="note_N10974_N1095C_N10953_N1091C_N1090C_N100F5_N10029_N10001" ixia_locid="120" type="caution">
                                <p ixia_locid="121">To ensure a successful installation, wait for
                                    the node to be reported as <uicontrol ixia_locid="803">Locked</uicontrol>, <uicontrol ixia_locid="126">Disabled</uicontrol>, and <uicontrol ixia_locid="128">Online</uicontrol>, and ensure that the login prompt
                                    appears on the host console. If the process is interrupted
                                    prematurely, the host installation can fail.</p>
                            </note>
                        </info>
                        <stepresult ixia_locid="804">
                            <p ixia_locid="805">On the host console, a login screen is
                                displayed.</p>
                            <note id="note_N10999_N10990_N10953_N1091C_N1090C_N100F5_N10029_N10001" ixia_locid="806">
                                <p ixia_locid="807">You must change your password immediately. To
                                    begin, provide the default password <nameliteral ixia_locid="808">wrsroot</nameliteral>. Then type a new
                                    password and confirm it.</p>
                            </note>
                        </stepresult>
                    </substep>
                </substeps>
                <stepresult id="node_locked_available_online" ixia_locid="110">
                    <p ixia_locid="97">The host is now configured with a personality.</p>
                </stepresult>
            </step>
        </steps>
    </taskbody>
